  <h1>
    Background
  </h1>

  <p>
    In mid-2021, our "Teams Group" tackled declining Teams SKU retention while 
    leadership noticed increased purchases of the "Professional" SKU designed 
    for freelancers. As the team focusing on "work," we were best suited to 
    explore this opportunity.
  </p>

  <p>
    Frances Klein, my product partner, assembled a "tiger team" of product, 
    design, data, and research at the end of 2021. Marian Oman, our Research 
    Lead for Teams, discovered that remote work fostered temporary working 
    relationships, and Pros and Teams faced similar needs but encountered 
    collaboration challenges. Christina Choi, our Data Science lead, confirmed 
    low retention despite many former Teams users buying Pro.
  </p>

  <p>
    We tasked the tiger team with diagnosing collaboration challenges between 
    Pros and Teams and devising principles and actions. Within weeks, we 
    established a high-level strategy, gained leadership alignment, and assigned 
    two squads to enhance collaboration between Teams and Pros. One would take a 
    "Pro-first" approach, the other a "Teams first". It was a cross-functional 
    project involving Product Design, Research, Content Design, Product, Product 
    Marketing, Customer Experience, Data Science, and Engineering.
  </p>

